snippet.textDisplay: I am not sure if you are still reading the comments or not, but if so I would like to ask you a question.  While you can’t always read tone in writing, please be assured that the question is asked so I can learn more.  As I understand the prefix “trans”, it means to span, like the TransCanada rail-line, or a trans-Atlantic ship.  So, your life spanned the sex assigned at birth, and the sex you knew yourself to be.  Once you have fully transition to the sex you knew yourself to be, aren’t you simply “a woman”?  That is, no longer spanning across, but fully yourself?
